---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words with X in the Middle — Hidden High Scorers"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing X in the middle position. From BOXER to TAXING, master mid-X words for surprise high-scoring plays. Free, no signup."
  keywords="words with x in middle scrabble, x in middle position, scrabble words x middle, mid-x words, high scoring x words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words with X in the Middle — Hidden High Scorers",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words with X in the middle position with point values and strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-22",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-x-in-the-middle" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best Scrabble words with X in the middle?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "BOXING (16 pts), TAXING (14 pts), FOXING (17 pts), VEXING (17 pts), and HEXING (17 pts) are top mid-X words. The -XING ending is particularly productive, generating many valid forms." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why are mid-X words valuable in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Mid-X words let you place the X tile (8 points) on premium squares more easily. When X is at the start or end, premium square alignment is limited. In the middle, you have more board positioning options to hit DLS or TLS with the X." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many Scrabble words have X in the middle position?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are over 150 valid Scrabble words with X in a middle position (not first or last letter). Common patterns include -OX- (BOXER, FOXES), -AX- (TAXED, WAXEN), and -EX- (HEXED, VEXED)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words with X in the Middle — Hidden High Scorers</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-22">June 22, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Most players think of X words as starting or ending with X — AX, OX, EX, WAX, FOX. But words with X buried in the middle offer a tactical advantage: more flexibility for premium square placement. When X sits in position 2, 3, or 4 of a word, you can align it with TLS or DLS squares that edge-X words can't reach.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">150+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid mid-X words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top scorer</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4-8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter range</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Mid-X Words by Score</h2>
      <p>These words place X in a middle position, giving you premium square flexibility that edge-X words lack.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">X Position</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FOXING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">VEXING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HEXING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BOXING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TAXING</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXHALE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2nd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXOTIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2nd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXYGEN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2nd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TAXIED</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIXIES</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3rd</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The -XING Pattern</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The <span class="text-white font-medium">-XING suffix pattern</span> is a goldmine. Take any 2-3 letter X-ending word and add -ING: BOX→BOXING, FOX→FOXING, HEX→HEXING, VEX→VEXING, TAX→TAXING, WAX→WAXING. Each one scores 14-17 points before premium squares.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HEXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VEXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WAXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NIXING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ TLS Targeting</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Mid-X words let you position X directly on Triple Letter Score squares. BOXING with X on TLS = 8×3 = 24 points from one tile alone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Cross-Score Potential</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X in the middle creates cross-word opportunities both above and below. A vertical BOXING can form AX or EX horizontally where the X crosses an existing row.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for Mid-X Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Think -XING first:</span> When you draw X, check if you have the tiles for any -XING word. These 6-letter plays consistently score 14-17 points and are easy to remember.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EX- words count as mid-X:</span> EXOTIC, EXHALE, EXILE, EXACT — these put X in position 2, which still gives you premium square flexibility compared to ending-X words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OXYGEN is a sleeper:</span> At 17 points base, OXYGEN uses common tiles (O, Y, G, E, N) alongside X. It's 6 letters and frequently overlooked because players don't associate it with X-word strategy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend short X words:</span> If someone plays BOX, you can hook -ING to make BOXING. If FOX is on the board, add -ED for FOXED (16 pts). Mid-X extensions are low-effort, high-reward plays.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-x/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">All Words Containing X — complete X word reference</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Words Ending With X — edge-X scoring strategies</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing X — Every Valid X Word</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-ex/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending in EX — High-Scoring EX Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-ax/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending in AX — Premium AX Plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
